        "title": "feat: metadata-enhanced repo search and double-click to open in browser",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nEnhances the repository search and browsing experience in Settings → Repositories with metadata-aware filtering and quick browser access.\r\n\r\n### Changes\r\n\r\n**Metadata-enhanced repository search** (commits `53c42f0`, `c9373fa`):\r\n- Added `description`, `language`, and `topics` fields from the GitHub API (mercy-preview header for topics)\r\n- `RepoAutocompleteScoring` now scores against topics (up to 400 pts), language (up to 150 pts), and description (60 pts)\r\n- Visual: language badges in autocomplete and AddRepoView; show description instead of owner/issues when available\r\n\r\n**Extended table search** (`41abca3`):\r\n- The \"Search repositories\" table filter also searches across `description`, `language`, and `topics`\r\n- Previously only searched `fullName`, `owner`, and `name` — now typing \"swift\" finds all Swift repos regardless of name\r\n\r\n**Double-click to open in browser** (`5d98082`):\r\n- Double-click any row in the repositories table to open it in your default browser\r\n- Respects GitHub Enterprise hosts via `RepoWebURLBuilder`\r\n",
